@title VoterSmartAccount
@author Katoh Thesis Project
@notice A minimal ERC-4337-style Smart Account for student voters.
@dev Each student gets a Smart Account deployed/resolved from their DID.
     The account:
     - Is controlled by the student's DID (derived from biometric + matric number)
     - Can execute calls to the Voting contract
     - Does not require the student to hold private keys or ETH
     This is a simplified implementation for the thesis prototype.

@notice Initialize the smart account with a DID hash
@param _didHash The Poseidon hash of the student's DID
@param _owner The address that controls this account (set by the system)

@notice Execute a call to another contract (e.g., Voting.castVote)
@param target The contract to call
@param value ETH value to send (usually 0 for voting)
@param data The calldata (e.g., castVote encoded)

@title SmartAccountFactory
@author Katoh Thesis Project
@notice Factory contract that deterministically deploys VoterSmartAccount
        instances based on DID hashes.
@dev Uses CREATE2 for deterministic addresses — given the same DID hash,
     the same Smart Account address is always computed.

@notice Deploy or retrieve a Smart Account for a given DID hash
@param _didHash The DID hash to associate with the account
@param _owner The address that will control the account
@return account The address of the Smart Account

@notice Compute the deterministic address of a Smart Account without deploying
@param _didHash The DID hash to compute the address for
@return The predicted address

@title VoterEligibility
@author Katoh Thesis Project
@notice Verifies student enrollment eligibility using zk-SNARK proofs and
        manages the set of eligible voters for an election.
@dev This contract:
  - Accepts a Groth16 proof proving a student holds valid enrollment data
    matching a known commitment, without revealing personal academic records.
  - Uses a nullifier hash to prevent a student from registering twice for the
    same election.
  - Maintains a registry of eligible DIDs that the Voting contract references.

@notice Register enrollment commitments (batch). Called during student enrollment.
@dev The commitment is Poseidon(matricNumber, departmentId, enrollmentSecret)
@param _commitments Array of enrollment commitments to register

@notice Verify a student's eligibility using a zk-SNARK proof and register
        them as an eligible voter.
@param _pA       Groth16 proof point A
@param _pB       Groth16 proof point B
@param _pC       Groth16 proof point C
@param _pubSignals Public signals: [enrollmentCommitment, nullifierHash, electionId]
@param _didHash  Hash of the student's Decentralised Identifier
@dev The proof demonstrates:
  1. The prover knows (matricNumber, departmentId, enrollmentSecret) whose
     Poseidon hash equals the public enrollmentCommitment.
  2. The nullifierHash is correctly derived from (matricNumber, electionId).

@notice Check if a DID is eligible to vote
@param _didHash Hash of the DID to check
@return True if the DID is registered as eligible

@title Voting
@author Katoh Thesis Project
@notice Core election contract that manages candidates, enforces one-vote-per-DID,
        and provides public self-tallying.
@dev This contract:
  - References VoterEligibility to confirm voter eligibility before accepting votes.
  - Enforces the one-vote-per-DID rule: once a DID has voted, any subsequent
    attempt is cryptographically rejected.
  - Provides a public self-tallying function that anyone can call to verify results.
  - Implements re-entrancy guards and access control as per Kushwaha et al. (2022).

@notice Initialize a new election with a time window
@param _electionId Unique election identifier (must match VoterEligibility)
@param _startTime Unix timestamp when voting opens
@param _endTime Unix timestamp when voting closes

@notice Add a candidate to the election
@param _candidateId Unique candidate identifier
@param _name Candidate's name
@param _party Candidate's party or affiliation

@notice Cast a vote for a candidate
@param _didHash Hash of the voter's Decentralised Identifier
@param _candidateId ID of the candidate to vote for
@dev This function:
  1. Checks the DID is eligible (via VoterEligibility contract)
  2. Enforces one-vote-per-DID
  3. Records the vote
  4. Uses re-entrancy guard
In the ERC-4337 flow, this is called via the EntryPoint contract on behalf
of the student's Smart Account, with gas sponsored by the Paymaster.

@notice Get the vote count for a specific candidate
@param _candidateId ID of the candidate
@return name The candidate's name
@return party The candidate's party
@return voteCount The number of votes received

@notice Get the full election results (self-tallying)
@return ids Array of candidate IDs
@return names Array of candidate names
@return parties Array of candidate parties
@return voteCounts Array of vote counts

@notice Get the winning candidate (self-tallying)
@return winnerId The ID of the candidate with the most votes
@return winnerName The name of the winning candidate
@return winnerVotes The vote count of the winner

@notice Check whether a given DID has voted
@param _didHash Hash of the DID to check
@return True if the DID has already cast a vote

@notice Validate whether a UserOperation should be sponsored
@dev In production ERC-4337, this would be called by the EntryPoint.
     For the thesis prototype, this simulates the validation logic.
@param userOp The UserOperation to validate
@return valid Whether the operation is approved for sponsorship

@notice Record gas sponsorship (called after successful operation)
@param sender The Smart Account address
@param gasUsed Amount of gas consumed

